title: In Israeli-occupied Hebron, Palestinians describe living in ‘a prison’
description: Israel has intensified its military occupation of Hebron in the West Bank — through arrests and crippling restrictions on the movement of Palestinians.

title: Four maps explain how Sweden and Finland will alter NATO’s security
description: The countries also offer key geographic advantages, which would enhance NATO’s defenses.

title: French Senate votes to enshrine abortion in constitution, a world first
description: Officials and activists predict the bill will successfully secure the backing of three-fifths of lawmakers from both houses of Parliament in a special congress next week at Versailles.

title: Russia seizes more villages in Ukraine, raising fears of growing momentum
description: The three villages, though strategically minor, still indicate that the Russian army is advancing while the Ukrainians are retreating.

title: Israeli filmmaker engulfed in backlash after antiwar speech in Berlin
description: Yuval Abraham also criticized his government’s treatment of Palestinians at the Berlin film festival. He said ensuing death threats made it unsafe for him to return home.

title: Prince Harry not owed full royal security protection, U.K. court says
description: Harry has tried to keep the same level of security in Britain that he had when he was a “working royal,” which included blanket protection by specially trained police officers.

title: PETA says it ‘rescued’ racing pigeons from King Charles, urges end to sport
description: PETA is urging King Charles III to cut ties with pigeon racing. A Sandringham spokesperson said the royal pigeon loft “adheres to all standards.”

title: Russian opposition leader Navalny’s funeral set for Friday in Moscow
description: Navalny spokeswoman Kira Yarmysh said a funeral will take place at the Church of the Icon of the Mother of God in Navalny’s home district of Maryino.

title: Middle East conflict live updates: Israel and Hamas downplay progress toward cease-fire deal
description: President Biden, under domestic political pressure over his handling of the war in Gaza, had said he hoped a weeks-long cease-fire could start as soon as next week.

title: South African city copes with climate change by chopping down trees
description: Cape Town is running low on water, so conservationists are clearing invasive species that are sucking it dry.

title: Irene Camber, grande dame of women’s fencing, dies at 98
description: At the 1952 Olympic Games in Helsinki, she became the first Italian woman to win a gold medal in foil fencing.

title: Foreign troops in Ukraine? They’re already there.
description: Stories of foreign nationals from Syria, Cuba, Nepal, India joining in Ukraine chart the tangled, tragic global fault lines of the war.

title: ‘Dreadful’ Wonka-themed children’s event leads some guests to call police
description: An underwhelming Willy Wonka-themed children’s event in Glasgow, Scotland, went viral after guests said they were misled by advertisements.
